                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50654",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=scollins",
                        "name": "scollins",
                        "displayName": "Scott Collins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please excuse this if it has been addressed in another bug, but i think that I have found the issue.\r\n\r\nIn the the isValid function in  Zend_Validate_Hostname, if the name is not an ip address, ie. 'localhost' rather than '127.0.0.1', then the error message is set to Zend_Validate_Hostname::INVALID_HOSTNAME . If the check against local network name schema passes, then the 'status' variable is set to true. In my case, I have set to $_allow set to Zend_Validate_Hostname::ALLOW_ALL, which , when anded with Zend_Validate_Hostname::ALLOW_LOCAL withh return true. This gives us a case where the hostname is valid , however an error is reported",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=scollins",
                        "name": "scollins",
                        "displayName": "Scott Collins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-15T03:38:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-15T03:38:15.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
